In [15]:
count = []
per = []
for i in df.columns:
    miss_num = df[i].isnull().sum()
    miss_per = df[i].isnull().sum() / len(df)*100
    count.append(miss_num)
    per.append(miss_per)
    
table = pd.DataFrame({'column': df.columns, 
                     'no of missing values': count,
                     'per of missing values': per})

### Linear Regression
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split, cross_val_score
x_train,x_test,y_train,y_test = train_test_split(x,y,train_size=0.8, random_state=4)

from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression
lin = LinearRegression()
lin.fit(x_train,y_train)

lin_ycap_train = lin.predict(x_train)
lin_ycap_test = lin.predict(x_test)

print('train_acc:', lin.score(x_train, y_train)*100)
print('test_acc:', lin.score(x_test, y_test)*100)
print('cvs:', cross_val_score(lin,x,y,cv=5).mean()*100)
